@{
    ViewBag.Title = "About";
}

<main aria-labelledby="title">
    <h2 id="title">@ViewBag.Title.</h2>

    <p>Welcome to Daily Planner, a web application designed to help you organize your daily tasks and manage your schedule efficiently. This project was created with the goal of providing a user-friendly and intuitive tool for keeping track of your daily activities.</p>

    <p>Key features of Daily Planner include:</p>

    <ul>
        <li>Task Management: Create, edit, and delete tasks to keep track of your daily to-dos.</li>
        <li>Responsive Design: Access Daily Planner from any device, including desktops, laptops, tablets, and smartphones.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>This project is built using the following technologies:</p>

    <ul>
        <li>ASP.NET MVC: Provides the framework for building the web application.</li>
        <li>.NET Framework: Used for the backend development to handle business logic and data operations.</li>
        <li>Microsoft SQL Server: The database management system used to store and manage task data.</li>
        <li>HTML, CSS, and JavaScript: Used for the frontend development to create the user interface and add interactivity.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>The project follows the Model-View-Controller (MVC) architectural pattern, which helps in organizing the codebase into separate components for easier maintenance and scalability. ASP.NET MVC provides a robust framework for building dynamic web applications, while .NET Framework offers a powerful platform for developing backend logic.</p>

    <p>Microsoft SQL Server is used as the backend database to store and manage task data. It provides a reliable and scalable solution for data storage and retrieval, ensuring that your task information is stored securely and can be accessed quickly when needed.</p>

    <p>Thank you for using Daily Planner. We hope it helps you stay organized and productive!</p>
</main>
